<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000063#     2#         1602#">Va. Code Ann. § 63.2-1602</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_63.2-1602"/><heading><desig>§ 63.2-1602.</desig><title>Other adult services</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><bodyText><p>Subject to the supervision and in accordance with regulations of the Commissioner for Aging and Rehabilitative Services as provided in Article 4 (<citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 51.5-144"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 51.5-144">§ 51.5-144<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000051#     5#          144#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> et seq.) of Chapter 14 of Title 51.5, each local board shall:</p></bodyText><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_1"/><heading><desig>1.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Participate in nursing home pre-admission screenings of all individuals pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 32.1-330"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 32.1-330">§ 32.1-330<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000032#     1#          330#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>;</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_2"/><heading><desig>2.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Provide assisted living facility assessments of residents and applicants pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 63.2-1804"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 63.2-1804">§ 63.2-1804<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000063#     2#         1804#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>;</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_3"/><heading><desig>3.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Participate in long-term care service coordination pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 51.5-138"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 51.5-138">§ 51.5-138<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000051#     5#          138#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>;</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_4"/><heading><desig>4.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Provide social services or public assistance, as appropriate, to individuals discharged from state hospitals or training centers pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 37.2-505"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 37.2-505">§§ 37.2-505<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000037#     2#          505#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 37.2-837"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 37.2-837">37.2-837<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000037#     2#          837#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; and</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_5"/><heading><desig>5.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Participate in other programs pursuant to state and federal law.</p></bodyText></level></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="2002 VA CH 747"><content><span normalizedCite="2002 Va. Ch. 747">2002, c. 747<locator><locatorKey><keyName